---

## Assumptions

| # | Assumption | Confidence | Failure Mode |
|---|-----------|-----------|-------------|
| A1 | Users are authenticated before preference reads/writes | ~95% | Unauthenticated actors modify delivery channels |
| A2 | Channel providers (email/SMS/push) are unreliable | ~99% | Delivery treated as guaranteed; no retry/fallback |
| A3 | User-supplied contact data (phone, email, push token) is unvalidated | ~90% | Injection, delivery to wrong party, bounce storms |
| A4 | Rate limits are enforced server-side, not client-side | ~95% | Client bypass floods channels |
| A5 | Clock skew across services is bounded (<5s) | ~80% | Rate-limit windows miscalculate; duplicate delivery |
| A6 | Push tokens expire or rotate without notice | ~99% | Silent delivery failure with no feedback loop |
| A7 | Notification content may contain PII | ~95% | Logging/persistence leaks sensitive data |

## Failure Modes

| Assumption | Failure | Impact | Fallback |
|-----------|---------|--------|----------|
| A1 | Unauthenticated preference mutation | Spam/silence | AuthZ gate on all preference and dispatch endpoints |
| A2 | Provider outage | Notifications silently lost | Dead-letter queue + retry with exponential backoff; fallback channel |
| A3 | Invalid contact data | Bounce storms, carrier penalties | Verify-on-write (email confirmation, SMS OTP, push token validation) |
| A4 | Client-side rate limit bypass | Channel abuse, cost explosion | Server-side sliding window per (user, channel, notification_type) |
| A5 | Clock skew | Duplicate sends or dropped sends in window | Use monotonic counters alongside timestamps; idempotency keys |
| A6 | Stale push token | Silent failure | Provider feedback integration (APNs feedback, FCM errors); mark token invalid |
| A7 | PII in logs | Data breach | Redact content in logs; encrypt at rest; TTL on stored notifications |

## Fallbacks

Summarized in the table above. The critical architectural fallback: **every dispatch must be idempotent** (keyed on `idempotency_key`), and every channel failure must route to a dead-letter queue rather than silently dropping.

## Foundation

### Core Types

```typescript
type UserId = string; // opaque, externally issued
type NotificationId = string; // UUID v7 (time-sortable)
type IdempotencyKey = string; // caller-supplied or derived from (source_event_id + channel)

type Channel = "email" | "sms" | "push";

type NotificationPriority = "critical" | "high" | "normal" | "low";

type NotificationType =
  | "transactional"  // password reset, 2FA -- never suppressible
  | "system"         // outage, policy change -- rate-limited but not opt-out
  | "marketing"      // promotable content -- fully opt-out
  | "social";        // likes, comments -- per-user preference

// в”Җв”Җ Contact Data (trust boundary: user-supplied, must be verified) в”Җв”Җ

interface ContactData {
  email?: { address: string; verified: boolean; verifiedAt?: Date };
  sms?: { e164Phone: string; verified: boolean; verifiedAt?: Date };
  push?: PushToken[];
}

interface PushToken {
  token: string;
  platform: "apns" | "fcm" | "web";
  registeredAt: Date;
  lastSuccessAt?: Date;
  invalid: boolean;
}

// в”Җв”Җ User Preferences (trust boundary: authn required, schema-validated) в”Җв”Җ

interface ChannelPreference {
  enabled: boolean;
  quietHoursStart?: string; // HH:MM in user's timezone
  quietHoursEnd?: string;
}

interface UserNotificationPreferences {
  userId: UserId;
  timezone: string; // IANA, e.g. "America/New_York"
  channels: Record<Channel, ChannelPreference>;
  typeOverrides: Partial<Record<NotificationType, Partial<Record<Channel, boolean>>>>;
  updatedAt: Date;
}

// в”Җв”Җ Notification Envelope (internal, post-routing) в”Җв”Җ

interface NotificationEnvelope {
  id: NotificationId;
  idempotencyKey: IdempotencyKey;
  userId: UserId;
  type: NotificationType;
  priority: NotificationPriority;
  channel: Channel;
  content: NotificationContent;
  createdAt: Date;
  scheduledAt?: Date; // deferred for quiet hours
  status: "pending" | "dispatched" | "delivered" | "failed" | "dead_lettered";
  attempts: number;
  lastAttemptAt?: Date;
  providerResponse?: string; // opaque, from channel provider
}

interface NotificationContent {
  subject?: string;  // email only
  body: string;
  templateId?: string;
  templateVars?: Record<string, string>;
}

// в”Җв”Җ Rate Limit State в”Җв”Җ

interface RateLimitWindow {
  userId: UserId;
  channel: Channel;
  notificationType: NotificationType;
  windowStart: Date;
  windowDurationMs: number;
  count: number;
  limit: number;
}

// в”Җв”Җ Dead Letter Record в”Җв”Җ

interface DeadLetterRecord {
  envelope: NotificationEnvelope;
  reason: string;
  deadLetteredAt: Date;
  retriable: boolean;
}
```

